['Soil and climate

    A friable well drained red loamy soil in wet or garden lands under tropical conditions is ideal.

    It can be grown in regions receiving an annual rainfall of 1500 m

Season

    May-June is suitable

Seed Treatment

    Seed rhizomes dipped in phosalone 35 EC 2ml/lit or monocrotophos 36 WSC 1.5 ml/lit. 0.3% Copper oxychloride for 30 min or

    Seed treatment with P. fluorescens 10 g/kg and T. viride as 4 g/ Kg.

Propagation

    Mother rhizome & finger rhizomes. Seed rate of finger rhizome - 2000kg/ha.

Main Field Preparation:

    Main field is ploughed four times with chisel and disc plough each one time and cultivator twice.

    Ridges and furrows are formed at spacing of 45 cm (or) raised beds of 120 cm width are formed at an interval of 30 cm and the laterals are placed at the centre of each bed.

    The beds are wetted for 8-12 hours through drip irrigation depending upon soil moisture level.

Spacing

    45 x 15 cm. 25-30 g weight rhizomes are to be dibbled at a depth of 4 cm.']

['Fixed sampling aggregation method-

1- Visit the field in which the sampling is to be done by jig-jig and mark it at 10-15 places so that all parts of the farm can be included in it.

2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with the hands and put on clean clothes and make a round pile. Remove the clay from the finger to the four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure till almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. An information sheet along with the sample on which all the information is written, put it in a plastic bag and outside the clothes bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laboratory.']

Remove and destroy dead and severely affected branches of the tree
Remove alternate host, silk cotton and other hosts
Grow tolerant mango varieties viz., Neelam, Humayudin.
Swab Coal tar + Kerosene @ 1:2 or Carbaryl 50 WP 20 g / l (basal portion of the trunk - 3 feet height) after scraping the loose bark to prevent oviposition by adult beetles.

One celphos tablet (3 g aluminum phosphide) per hole
Apply carbofuran 3G 5 g per hole and plug with mud.']

1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.']

answers:
['Rattanidhi sampling aggregation method-

1- Visit the field in which the sampling is to be done by jig-jig and mark it at 10-15 places so that all parts of the farm can be included in it.

2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with the hands and put on clean clothes and make a round pile. Remove the clay from the finger to the four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure till almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. An information sheet along with the sample on which all the information is written, put it in a plastic bag and outside the clothes bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laboratory.

Soil investigation information sheet']
